-strings.md), [pointers.md](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/2b01a37ec38db9301239f0c0abcf3c695055b0ff/src/doc/trpl/pointers.md) and [unsafe.md](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/2b01a37ec38db9301239f0c0abcf3c695055b0ff/src/doc/trpl/unsafe.md) could use this feature. Although I'm not sure where that should be told, maybe pointers.md?\n\nUnrelated, old guides like [guide-crates.md](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/2b01a37ec38db9301239f0c0abcf3c695055b0ff/src/doc/guide-crates.md) link to a nonexisting directory (src/doc/book) when they should actually point to src/doc/trpl\n", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/22637/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/22637/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}